== <font face="Times Chomsky">'''Description'''</font> ==
{{Blurimage|file=Industrialrain.jpeg|caption=An image taken within the industrial side at night.|align=right}}
Level 146, otherwise known as "Eternal Downpour" takes the appearance of an abandoned city which is split into two parts, those being the industrial area and the suburban area. The industrial side bears a similar appearance to [[Level 11]], appearing as a desolate cityscape possessing various buildings, the architectural design within the industrial side varies. Most of the designs within the level closely resemble those within the United States, although a few outliers have been found. These outliers do not match the architectural design anywhere on [[The Frontrooms|earth]] and appear otherworldly. Wanderers have reported finding labels on those buildings with unknown characters. Researchers have made numerous attempts to decipher the labels, however every attempt has failed. Resulting in the symbols being up for interpretation. Large empty parking lots may also be found within the industrial side. No plants have been encountered within the industrial area, the sole exception being moss. The suburban side of the level is similar in appearance to [[Level 9]], appearing as a network of winding asphalt roads which feature residential homes, a multitude of park's may also be found within the suburban side. Every park is estimated to be about 5 meters in length and width. The terrain of the parks is reported as being entirely flat.

{{Blurimage|file=AbandonedRain.jpg|caption=An image taken of one of the buildings.|align=right}}The entire level spans an approximate distance of 1 AU. Upon entering the level, wanderers appear in random spots of the city. If a wanderer manages to reach or appear near the end of the level, they would encounter an invisible border, the level's terrain abruptly stops upon reaching the border, beyond the invisible wall is an endless expanse of what appears to manifest in the form of the sky. Throughout the dead city, buildings lay scattered, appearing typical from the exterior despite possessing an incredibly old and withered interior. The interior of the buildings typically lack any furnishing, containing only supplies which may be encountered during varying time periods. Moss and mould have additionally been documented to appear on the interiors, likely due to the endless downpour dampening the buildings. The material of the buildings typically consist of mainly bricks, although some are known to be easily damaged by [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]], leaving certain buildings vulnerable during midnight. The level additionally experiences a constant supply of rain. Interestingly, the rain is known to exhibit an anomalous property allowing it to clip through buildings, this property is known to cease functioning during midnight, allowing wanderers safety under non-corroding surfaces. Due to the perpetual downfall, buildings throughout Level 146 have become steadily more frail. Upon entry, all wanderers have reported entering during the day, leading researchers to believe it is impossible to enter at any other period of time. Wanderers also report experiencing a peaceful sensation throughout their body upon first entering the level. Wanderers have reported finding a giant drain at the centre of the level, it is believed that this drain is what prevents the level from flooding, objects which obstruct the drain are documented to suddenly vanish, re-appearing approximately 1km away. Surviving this level becomes an increasingly difficult task as the day and night cycle progresses. 

== <font face="Chomsky">'''Day/Night Cycle'''</font> ==

=== <font face="Chomsky">'''Day Time'''</font> ===
{{Blurimage|file=Dayrain.jpg|caption=An image taken during the day.|align=right|154x154px|}}Day lasts for approximately 2 hours. During this period, the sky is reported as appearing as a dull blue, covered in a variety of dark clouds. A thick fog is known to additionally envelop the level. Level 146 exhibits yet another time-exclusive anomalous property of its rain transforming suddenly into [[Object 1|Almond Water]] whilst a wanderer has sustained an injury, interestingly lasting for an interval of 5 seconds. A large supply of various items one may use to survive may be encountered within the abandoned buildings, anomalously disappearing into twilight and night. Throughout the day [[Entity 9|Facelings]] are reported as displaying no aggression, appearing docile in all circumstances.

 

 

=== <font face="Times New Roman">'''Dusk'''</font> ===
{{Blurimage|file=AtDusk.jpg|caption=An image taken at dusk.|align=right|154x154px|}}Dusk lasts for 90 minutes. During this period, the sky is documented to change from a grey to a dull orange in the transition into dusk. The light rain transforms into a stormy environment, the wind picks up as the rain increases in intensity. Lightning strikes are additionally reported to occasionally occur. [[Entity 9|Facelings]] are no longer docile and will attack if provoked, however these [[Entity 9|Facelings]] can be evaded. [[Entity 8|Hounds]] may additionally be encountered whilst wandering the streets and within buildings during dusk.

 

 

=== <font face="Chomsky">'''Twilight'''</font> ===
{{Blurimage|file=Twilighttime.jpg|caption=An image taken during twilight.|align=right|154x154px|}}Twilight lasts for 30 minutes. The sky appears dark blue with a faint orange glow on the horizon during twilight. [[Entity 4|Death Moths]] and [[Phenomenon 35|Wretches]] are known to begin appearing throughout the level. A majority of recourses within buildings are reported to vanish into twilight. [[Entity 9|Facelings]] are reported to attack wanderers who approach them, however they have been observed to simply ignore those who avoid them. As twilight progresses, one's mind may begin to deteriorate, slowly falling into a panicked state, escalating for 20 minutes despite possessing no source. One is capable of regulating and decreasing the panic, however it is currently considered impossible to force it to fully subside, with the only method being to survive until after night, which the effect continues into.

 

 

=== <font face="Chomsky">'''Night time'''</font> ===
{{Blurimage|file=Didnt you see the news today.png|caption=An image taken at night.|align=right|154x154px|}}Night lasts for 2 hours. The level falls into an encompassing darkness, leaving the only light sources being lamp posts and occasional lightning strikes, which occur increasingly more frequent into the night. The wind picks up further as the rain increases further in intensity. All sources of [[Object 1|Almond Water]] have been reported to suddenly vanish when night starts, including [[Object 1|Almond Water]] one may have already obtained. Numerous new entities appear, all entities one may encounter are listed below <ul><li>[[Entity 3|Smilers]]</li><li>[[Entity 10|Skin Stealers]]</li><li>[[Entity 6|Dullers]]</li><li>[[Entity 29|Mannequins]]</li></ul>
[[Entity 9|Facelings]] are known to act hostile during this time, attacking any wanderer within their range of sight. Wanderers are strongly recommended to immediately seek shelter indoors and board off any potential entrances to prevent entities from entering.

 

 

=== <font face="Times New Roman">'''Midnight'''</font> ===
{{Blurimage|file=An image taken at midnight.png|caption=An image taken at midnight.|align=right|154x154px|}}Midnight lasts for 1 hour. The rain is documented to abruptly switch into [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]], Resulting in the death of all the entities and destroying all of the light sources and resulting in the level becoming shrouded in complete darkness. The rain  possesses an anomalous property which allows it to appear still visible despite the noticeable absence of light.  As  stated previously the rain loses its anomalous property to clip through walls and buildings, allowing wanderers safety whilst sheltered under a non-corroding material. During midnight, wanderers report hearing anomalous auditory hallucinations, encouraging and attempting to lure them to leave their shelter, exposing themselves to the outside. Listening to the whispers is highly discouraged and will lead to ones death due to the rain, Any attempt to leave Level 101 during this time will result in one's transportation to a random Class 5 or Deadzone level.

 

 

=== <font face="Chomsky">'''Sunrise'''</font> ===
{{Blurimage|file=Sunrise.png|caption=An image taken of a pothole filled with [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]] during sunrise.|align=right|154x154px|}}Sunrise lasts for 30 minutes. The sky consists of a gradient ranging from an orange horizon, transitioning into a blackened sky. The rain is documented to shift from [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]] back to regular rainwater. The level will begin to slowly regenerate during the entire period of sunrise. If an object is within a position in which it would obstruct a structure's reformation, the object will suddenly vanish, being destroyed in order to complete the regeneration process. Additionally, one may encounter puddles of [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]] which can be found throughout the level.

 

 

=== <font face="Chomsky">'''Morning'''</font> ===
{{Blurimage|file=Realmorning.jpg|caption=An image taken in the morning.|align=right|154x154px|}}Morning lasts for 90 minutes. One's mind will instantly enter a relaxed state when a wanderer reaches morning. The sky appears bright and the clouds are reported to clear, unveiling the bright sky. Despite the clear sky, rain still pours. The rain’s velocity has decreased significantly into a light drizzle and the wind is documented to transform into a light breeze. The rain is reported to transition into [[Object 1|Almond Water]]. Rainbows are additionally reported to begin appearing in the sky. A plethora of supplies have been documented to appear suddenly within buildings. All supplies which have so far appeared are documented to possess only one use: treating wounds. Wanderers who travel an unknown distance, likely 3 kilometres during this period have reported encountering a building possessing no windows, entry is impossible, as the entrance door is locked and attempting to force entry by any method has been reported to transport wanderers to a different location. Additionally, explosives have been reported to vanish before detonation. It is theorised that entities are created within this building, although it is impossible to confirm as entrance is impossible and wanderers are reportedly forced out of the level after morning is over.

== <font face="Chomsky">'''Entities'''</font> ==
Different Entities appear as the days cycle progresses. 
<ul>
<li>Day - Only docile [[Entity 9|Facelings]] appear at this time.</li>

<li>Dusk - [[Entity 8|Hounds]] start appearing alongside [[Entity 9|Facelings]] becoming neutral.</li>

<li>Twilight - [[Entity 4|Death Moths]] and [[Phenomenon 35|Wretches]] appear and [[Entity 9|Facelings]] begin to attack any wanderer that comes close.</li>

<li>Night - [[Entity 3|Smilers]], [[Entity 10|Skin Stealers]], [[Entity 6|Dullers]] and [[Entity 29|Mannequins]] appear alongside [[Entity 9|Facelings]] becoming aggressive.</li>

<li>Midnight, sunrise and morning - Devoid of entities.</li>
</ul>

== <font face="Chomsky">'''Entrances and exits'''</font> ==

=== <font face="Chomsky">'''Entrances'''</font> ===
<ul>
<li>No-Clipping in [[Level 11]] possesses an approximate 30% chance to transport one to Level 146 within the industrial area.</li>

<li>No-clipping in [[Level 9]] possesses an approximate 30% chance to transport one to Level 146 within the suburban area.</li>
</ul>

=== <font face="Chomsky">'''Exits'''</font> ===
<ul>
<li>Surviving the entire day cycle from day to morning will transport one to [[Level 696]].</li>

<li>No-clipping out of the level at any time except midnight will transport one to a random sub level of [[Level 11]].</li>
<li>Obstructing the drain possesses an approximate 25% chance to transport one to [[Level 7]].
</ul>
